OL,3,C'He was neglected': Adults with
OL,4,Clearning disabilities dying 20 years
OL,5,Cearly
OL,7,F"These stark new figures show people
OL,8,Fwith a learning disability are dying a
OL,9,Fshocking 19.5 years younger than the
OL,10,Fgeneral population and are three times
OL,11,Fmore likely to die from a condition
OL,12,Fwhich could have been treated. People
OL,13,Fwith a learning disability and their
OL,14,Ffamilies deserve better. In this day
OL,15,Fand age, no one should die early
OL,16,Fbecause they don't get the right
OL,17,Ftreatment.
