OL,3,C'He was neglected': Adults with
OL,4,Clearning disabilities dying 20 years
OL,5,Cearly
OL,7,F"He was declining so rapidly, he
OL,8,Fdidn't understand what was happening.
OL,9,FYou could see he was really ill, he
OL,10,Fdidn't respond, he was semi-conscious
OL,11,Fand drowsy," said Mary.
OL,13,F"My sister wiped his mouth because it
OL,14,Fseemed there was something on his
OL,15,Flips, and a whole paracetamol fell out.
OL,17,F"It was neglect," said Teresa.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/18
