OL,3,C'He was neglected': Adults with
OL,4,Clearning disabilities dying 20 years
OL,5,Cearly
OL,7,F"One time, a doctor was speaking to my
OL,8,Fsister, and I was awake. He told her
OL,9,Fthat she should contemplate letting me
OL,10,Fgo because of my quality of life. This
OL,11,Fwas so upsetting to hear because I was
OL,12,Fright there.
OL,14,F"It felt like they had just given up
OL,15,Fon me and that I was invisible. Also,
OL,16,Fthe fact that he didn't respect me
OL,17,Fenough to speak to me or involve me.
OL,18,FFelt like I was not a person but a
OL,19,Fthing. This was not a one-off.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
