OL,3,C'He was neglected': Adults with
OL,4,Clearning disabilities dying 20 years
OL,5,Cearly
OL,7,F"Often, doctors and nurses would not
OL,8,Ftalk to me directly and assume I would
OL,9,Fnot understand.
OL,11,F"The NHS is not built to look after
OL,12,Fpeople with a learning disability the
OL,13,Fway it needs to. Disabilities are
OL,14,Fcomplex and unique, so treatment
OL,15,Fshould be tailored to them. One size
OL,16,Ffits all approach does not work."
OL,18,FThe LeDeR report was established in
OL,19,F2015 to tackle the gap in health
OL,20,Finequalities for learning disabled and
OL,21,Fautistic people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/18
